I don't really know your problem.
RegistryProtocol is also a wrapper.
ProtocolFilterWrapper have a constructor with protocol so the RegistryProtocol also can be wrapped.
It dependency the ProtocolFilterWrapper's constructor but not RegistryProtocol's constructor.

But RegistryProtocol's export and refer method will not be filted because of code in ProtocolFilterWrapper:

```
@Override
public <T> Exporter<T> export(Invoker<T> invoker) throws RpcException {
    if (Constants.REGISTRY_PROTOCOL.equals(invoker.getUrl().getProtocol())) {
        return protocol.export(invoker);
    }
    //...
}

@Override
public <T> Invoker<T> refer(Class<T> type, URL url) throws RpcException {
    if (Constants.REGISTRY_PROTOCOL.equals(url.getProtocol())) {
        return protocol.refer(type, url);
    }
    //...
}
```

The same code can be found in ProtocolListenerWrapper.

